e medieval German lied in terms of its motifs, its reception and its function in society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aMiddle Ages. 0aSongs, German. 4aFrühneuhochdeutsch. 4aLied. 4aMittelhochdeutsch. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAshcroft, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaldzuhn, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehr, Hans-Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBremer, Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aByrn, Richard F.Μ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Cyril, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Cyril, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFlood, John L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHages, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaustein, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHellgardt, Ernst, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHirschberg, Dagmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasten, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnape, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMärz, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrtmann, Christa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOtt, Norbert H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRanawake, Silvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/